    "intro": "Once a bottle of wine is opened, oxidation begins as the wine is exposed to air and after a couple of days the flavour deteriorates. Boxed wine or \"goon bag\" wine (arguably the greatest invention to come from Australia) solves the oxidation problem by containing the wine in an airtight blader, this dramatically extends shelf life after opening. The problem is most wine sold as boxed wine is usually cheaper and not as enjoyable as wine found in more expensive glass bottles. This simple project preserves quality wine, so it can be enjoyed over many days, by transferring it into a \"goon bag\".",
